results.synopsisLong: In this comedy-adventure, Timon and Pumbaa reveal where they came from, where they met and how they helped Simba save the Serengeti. Their story includes glimpses into some big events from The Lion King that look a little different from Timon and Pumbaa's perspective - such as when King Mufasa introduced baby Simba to the animal kingdom. Let's just say there was something behind that dramatic moment when all the animals bowed to their new ruler! Nathan Lane, Matthew Broderick, Ernie Sabella and the original voice cast return for this hysterical musical tale - and meet colorful new characters like Timon's Ma (Julie Kavner) and Uncle Max (Jerry Stiller)! With all your favorite characters, the music you love and more, get ready for some king-sized fun with Timon and Pumbaa!

results.synopsisLong: While foraging for bugs in a Brazilian rainforest, Timon and Pumbaa come across a big "Bug Buffet." It seems too good to be true, and of course, it is: the Bug Buffet is a clever trap set by Sleeky and Gulp, two carnivorous South American jungle snakes. When Pumbaa eats too many bugs and gets sick, it is up to Timon to take care of him. Timon's overzealous bedside manner makes Pumbaa proud (and a little annoyed). When Pumbaa gets better by himself, he doesn't have the heart to tell his bestest pal.
